Wash and dry produce. Quarter @lime{1}. Finely dice @roma tomato{1}. Peel and
finely dice @kiwi{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}; mince a few
slices until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4 servings). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.
Core, deseed, and finely chop @poblano pepper{1}.

== Lime Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and a squeeze of lime juice.
Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Kiwi Salsa ==

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together tomato, kiwi, minced onion, half the cilantro,
and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

== Chicken Filling ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add sliced onion, poblano, and half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly charred, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add chicken breast strips{10%ounce}, a large drizzle of oil, and remaining
Southwest Spice to pan with veggies. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until
chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with salt and
pepper.

> Pat chicken dry with paper towels.

> Swap in chicken for pork; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is
> browned and cooked through.

Reduce heat under pan to medium low. If there's excess grease in your pan,
carefully pour it out.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, and
@water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring, until everything is coated in a thick sauce,
~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with chicken filling, salsa, and crema.
Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.